// AliasEditor
// Inline editor for managing a list of string aliases on a Kodex topic.
// Displays existing aliases as chips with remove buttons, and an expandable
// inline input to add new ones. Prevents duplicates and empty values.

FUNCTION AliasEditor(aliases, onAdd, onRemove) -> JSX                  EXPORT
  CALLS: AliasChip (AliasChip)
  Renders existing aliases as AliasChip components. Chips are disabled while
  any add/remove operation is in flight.
  Shows a "+ Add" button when collapsed. On click, expands to show a text input
  plus Submit/Cancel buttons. Auto-focuses the input when expanded.

---

FUNCTION handleAddClick() -> void
  Sets isExpanded to true (reveals the input row).

---

FUNCTION handleInputKeyDown(e) -> void
  IF Enter: calls handleSubmit.
  IF Escape: calls handleCancel.

---

FUNCTION handleSubmit() -> void
  Trims input value. Returns early if empty or already in aliases list.
  Sets isLoading true, calls onAdd(trimmedValue).
  On completion, clears input and collapses form.

---

FUNCTION handleCancel() -> void
  Clears input value and collapses the form.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveAlias(alias) -> void
  Sets removingAlias to the alias being removed.
  Calls onRemove(alias). Clears removingAlias on completion.
